headline: Berkshire May Have Sold Apple, Bank of America Stock in Third Quarter
summary: Berkshire Hathaway  sold $12 billion of stocks in the third quarter, and  Apple  and  Bank of America  lead the list of potential sale candidates.  Berkshire likely will release its quarterly 13-F report late Friday detailing its equity holdings of U.S.-listed securities as of Sept. 30.  Friday is the deadline for 13-F filings, and Berkshire typically waits until the final day to file.
